# LazyGolf

> A multi-vertical golf lifestyle brand combining apparel, technology platform, and entertainment content for casual golfers who don't take the game too seriously.

---

## Executive Summary

**LazyGolf** is the flagship venture of [[Kikman Enterprises]], targeting the massively underserved market of casual, fun-focused golfers. Unlike traditional golf brands that emphasize performance, prestige, and seriousness, LazyGolf embraces the laid-back approach to the game.

### The Opportunity

The golf industry is experiencing a renaissance, with **47.2 million Americans** playing golf in 2024 - a record high ([National Golf Foundation](https://www.ngf.org/the-clubhouse/golf-industry-research/)). The **leisure segment dominates with 80.1% of revenue share**, and the **mass market captures 62.83%** of equipment sales, yet most golf brands still target serious, competitive players.

### Our Thesis

> "Golf brands make the mistake of generic messaging. You could easily replace one brand name with another and no one would know the difference." - [BN Branding](https://bnbranding.com/brandinsightblog/golf-industry-marketing-strategy/)

LazyGolf will be the anti-golf golf brand - authentic, irreverent, and focused on **fun over score**.

### Business Model

| Vertical | Revenue Model | Year 1 Target |
|----------|---------------|---------------|
| **Apparel** | E-commerce (POD → Inventory) | $30,000-50,000 |
| **Platform** | Freemium SaaS | 1,000+ users (free) |
| **Media** | Ad revenue + brand funnel | 5,000+ subscribers |

**Tagline Options:**
- "Golf for the rest of us"
- "Swing lazy, score happy"
- "Less effort, more fun"
- "The anti-golf golf brand"

