### Tone of Voice Guidelines

#### Do Say

- "Life's too short for slow golf and high scores"
- "We're here for the vibes, not the victories"
- "Your handicap is our business (literally)"
- "Golf is hard. Laughing about it is easy."

#### Don't Say

- Anything mean-spirited about good golfers
- Overly crude humor
- Anything exclusionary
- Generic golf marketing speak

### Brand Story

> LazyGolf was born on a random Tuesday afternoon when two friends were playing their usual terrible round of golf. After losing three balls, shanking into a cart path, and four-putting from 10 feet, they realized something: they were having the best time.
>
> That's when it hit them - golf doesn't have to be serious. The expensive equipment, the strict etiquette, the pressure to improve... none of that matters when you're out there with friends, enjoying the sunshine, and laughing at your own terrible shots.
>
> LazyGolf is for every golfer who's ever claimed a foot wedge, called gimme from 8 feet, or mysteriously found their ball in a great lie. It's for the millions of us who play for fun, not for our handicap.
>
> Welcome to the lazy side.

